This paper is about malware classification using machine learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically uses a deep learning architecture (LSTM) and investigates the use of different input formats (text and hexadecimal) for classification, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of the Python package Keras for training, which is commonly used in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper deals with the increasing interconnectivity of cyber-systems, which suggests a focus on networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
